    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3227420/extras/55acbfba2b0fe743685cf8a85402b473.avif?t=1739512766\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3227420/extras_big/55acbfba2b0fe743685cf8a85402b473.avif?t=1739512766 width=800 height=245 /></span>In Copper Odyssey 2, you will be playing as Celeste, the little sister of Herman the Printmaking Angel. She has gotten a job outside of the print studio and into Nickel City. Her first day will be turning blank canvases into paintings. Go through the museum and do the best job you can. She’ll be able to make some friends along the way. <strong>Reveal the 30 paintings and you'll be done for the day.</strong><br><br>This game uses <strong>JRPG combat to destroy enemies</strong>. There are many enemies who are beautiful artworks, they want to take Celeste to the Unicorn’s art studio…but she has a job to do.   <br> <span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3227420/extras/58f3068c90f48e83d203d25f3bf5696c.avif?t=1739512766\" width=360 height=360 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This game, like the previous Copper Odyssey, is open-ended. You can handle things in any order you want, as long as you <strong>respect the craft!</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
